    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then chop your <strong>cavolo nero </strong>roughly, removing any tough stalks</p><p>Line a baking tray with a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong>, then add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>cavolo nero</strong> to the middle of the foil with a few small knobs of <strong>butter</strong> and 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the kale to form a sealed parcel then put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until tender</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
