      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot </strong>with a few knobs<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Add the<strong> remaining double cream</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> cracked black pepper</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[70ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[90ml]<strong> </span>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>peppercorn sauce</strong></p>",
